13:
A Doomsday Lance?! I-I've never
seen one so big, though.
16:
Evidently, it's known as the
Doomsday Spire.
20: Stella! I'm so glad you're safe.
24: Likewise. Everyone else is here too.
28:
Oh, Stella... We did it! We... we really
made it.
33:
Heh. Anyways, that tower's
apparently where all the Doomsday
Lances on the surface keep comin'
from.
37:
The surface? Do you mean to imply
this world is located beneath mine?
41:
Not beneath, but within—at least in
terms of their coordinates. You
cannot travel between them
physically.
45:
I don't really get it, but that would
explain why there's no sky, no light,
no fresh air.
48:
It makes sense, though. That'd be
why Adjudicus and the other rebels
are gearing up to take control of the
Spire.
51:
If that thing can send Doomsday
Lances to your world, it should be
able to send us too.
55:
Moreover, we could prevent further
invasions, and keep the forces
already there from regrouping with
the main army here.
60:
Only thing is, they need Stella's
power to use the Doomsday Spire.
66:
Who knows. Adjudicus won't give
any of us the time of day. All he
cares about are Stella and the
smart-ass elf kid.
70:
Hmm... Try not to worry about it,
Stella.
75:
I'm not worried about the Doomsday
Spire. There's just... something else
on my mind.
77: We were unable to locate Marly.
80:
The scouts said she wasn't in the
village, and... and...
84:
It seems like she hasn't made it here
to the fortress either.
90:
You can't be serious, Light! What do
you mean, I should've killed those
soldiers?!
95:
I said it to Adjudicus and I'll say it
again. There was absolutely no
need to take their lives, and—
98:
They wouldn't have hesitated to
take yours, Alk.
101:
It's better them than you. This isn't
the time or place for naïve mercy.
104: Ah! I... didn't mean to raise my voice.
110:
What happened? It's not like the two
of you to fight.
113:
We were arguing over who'll go to
the Doomsday Spire. Light kept
saying it's too dangerous, but... *sigh*
115:
Sorry. I know this is hardly the time
to be fighting amongst ourselves...
118: I, for one, fully intend to go.
122: Wait, why?! I don't think that's a—
125:
Oh? It's fine for YOU to put yourself at
risk, but not me? Do elaborate.
128:
It's just... I mean, you're a princess,
right? Your people need you.
131:
Yes, and they need me here, Alk. Our
future belongs in our hands, not
delegated to allies.
133:
Which calls for negotiations. Both
with Light, and with Adjudicus.
136:
Negotiations, huh?
...You're right, Lilith. It's been a crazy
couple of days, but you really have
your head on straight.
140:
Heh. I finally found the courage to
be the leader I envisioned.
143:
I still have a ways to go, but... If you
wouldn't mind helping me, there's
something I'd like to try.
157:
Whoa. I-I had no idea you were THIS
strong.
160:
How did you DO that? It was
amazing!
164:
I'm glad to hear such praise from
you, what with all you've seen and
experienced in other worlds.
167:
Huh?! I'm not THAT good with a
sword, I've just travelled a lot is all.
170:
There's no need to be humble. Even
Shakari was impressed with your
skill, Alk.
174:
Shakari...
I... I'm sorry. If I'd been stronger, then
maybe...
177:
Please, don't blame yourself for
what happened.
179:
Shakari did things her own way, just
like she always has.
181:
She had no regrets, so neither
should we.
185:
Y'know... It feels like it's already been
so long since Shakari took me
hunting.
189:
She helped put together a little
feast, and even managed to teach
STELLA how to cook... I'm sure she
taught you well.
192:
She did. I learned everything I know
about swordplay from her. What
about you, Alk? What was it like
having the Champion himself as a
teacher?
195:
Oh, uh... I didn't meet Light until after
he lost his human form.
197:
But I guess he HAS taught me a lot,
and... I really look up to him.
200:
It sounds like we both have quite the
predecessors to live up to...
